":"1522","1500":"1500","1400":"1400","1455":"1455","1420":"1420","1475":"1475","1452":"1452","about 1455":"about 1455","after 1472":"after 1472","about 1452":"about 1452","Älvsborg, Sweden":"Älvsborg, Sweden","Älvsborg, Norrbotten, Sweden":"Älvsborg, Norrbotten, Sweden","Kastelholm, Åland, Finland":"Åland, Finland","Brodtorp-Pojo,Uusimaa, Finland":"Brödtorp, Uusimaa, Finland","Brödtorp, Uusimaa, Finland":"Brödtorp, Uusimaa, Finland","Brödtorp, Pohja, Uusimaa, Finland":"Pohja, Uusimaa, Finland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Ivarsson","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Americanized form (and a rare Swedish variant) of Swedish <b>Ivarsson</b>: patronymic from the personal name <i>Ivar</i>, from Old Norse <i>Ívarr</i>, a compound of either <i>ív</i> ‘yew tree, bow’ or <i>Ing</i> (the name of a god) + <i>ar</i> ‘warrior’ or ‘spear’. This is also an Americanized form of the rare Norwegian and Danish cognate <b>Ivarsen</b>. Compare   Iverson   1."],"variants":[{"name":"Iverson","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Iver, Erik, Hjalmer, Lars, Selmer, Thor, Evald, Gunner, Helmer, Ingman, Jarl, Joneen.","Americanized form of Norwegian, Danish, and North German   Iversen   and of Swedish <b>Ivarsson</b> (see   Ivarson  ), all cognates of 2 below.","English (Kent and London): patronymic from Old Norse <i>Ívarr</i>, <i>Iwar</i>, <i>Ivar</i>, a compound of either <i>ív</i> ‘yew tree, bow’ or <i>Ing</i> (the name of a god) + <i>ar</i> ‘warrior’ or ‘spear’. Alternatively, the name might be a patronymic from the Welsh male personal name <i>Ifor</i>, itself from British Celtic <i>Iūdomāros</i> ‘lord’ + ‘great’, but if so, it is not clear that it survives today."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1702076,"age":16,"year":"1436","julianDay":2245548,"title":"The Engelbrekt Rebellion","description":"Engelbrekt Engelbrektsson, a Swedish mine owner and statesman, led a rebellion against Eric of Pomerania, King